21/05/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- European Commission representative in Belgrade Geoffrey Barrett said Thursday (20 May) that Serbia-Montenegro is at crossroads regarding its Euro-integration. "The present government clearly understands all the obligations which need to be met on the road to the EU," said Barrett, who is leaving his post after three years.
In other news, a new poll finds Serbian presidential hopeful Boris Tadic of the Democratic Party would get 26 per cent of the votes, compared to 23 per cent for Serbian Radical Party nominee Tomislav Nikolic. A poll earlier this month put Nokolic in the lead. (B92, Glas Javnosti, Tanjug - 20/05/04)
